members.name: PeriodicSyncRegistration.minPeriod
members.description: Provides in miliseconds the minimum time between periodic sync events. User agents may delay this event for reasons ranging from usage frequency to device states such as, for example, battery charge, connectivity, and location.

members.name: PeriodicSyncRegistration.networkState
members.description: Indicates the network condition under which periodic background synchronization will occur. Valid values are 'any', 'avoid-cellular', and 'online'.

members.name: PeriodicSyncRegistration.powerState
members.description: Indicates how the PeriodicSyncRegistration deals with a devices' battery conditions. Valid values are 'auto', and 'avoid-draining'.

members.name: PeriodicSyncRegistration.tag
members.description: Provides the unique identifier of the specified PeriodicSyncRegistration.

members.name: PeriodicSyncRegistration.unregister
members.description: Returns a Promise that resolves to Boolean indicating whether the PeriodicSyncRegistration object was unregistered.
